content:
The Firebase Admin Node.js SDK is available on npm. If you don't already
have a package.json file, create one via npm init . Next, install the firebase-admin npm package and save it to your package.json : npm install firebase-admin --save To use the module in your application, require it from any JavaScript
file: const
{
initializeApp
}
=
require
(
'firebase-admin/app'
); If you are using ES2015, you can import the module: import
{
initializeApp
}
from
'firebase-admin/app'
;
